ilt - how do victims speak about it? How do the perpetrators? How do those who were able to keep their distance from National Socialism? How do they all speak about the guilt of the German people? The author investigates these questions and reconstructs three different sub-discourses in which participants construct the term, guilt, from their own different perspectives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aDiscourse analysiszGermany. 0aGuilt and culturezGermany. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xCauses. 0aNational socialismxMoral and ethical aspects. 4aDeutsch /Sprache. 4aDiskurs. 4aNachkriegszeit (Weltkrieg II). 4aSchuld. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh1 aKämper, Heidrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2005z9783110276886oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018855440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090733940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110907339423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110907339/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2005  aZDB-23-DGGb2005  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014